{"name":"Summon (Magic-User Level 1)","type":"spell","img":"/systems/lotfp/assets/default/spell.png","data":{"lvl":1,"class":"Magic-User","duration":"See Below","range":"10'","roll":"","description":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Magic fundamentally works by ripping a hole in the fabric of space and time and pulling out energy that interacts with and warps our reality. Various mages have managed to consistently capture specific energy in exact amounts to produce replicable results: Spells. The Summon spell opens the rift between the worlds a little bit more and forces an inhabitant From Beyond into our world to do the Magic-User's bidding. What exactly comes through the tear, and whether or not it will do what the summoner wishes, is wholly unpredictable. Once the Summon spell is cast, there are a number of steps to resolve:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&para; The caster chooses the intended Power of the Summoned Entity;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&para; The caster makes a saving throw versus Magic;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&para; Determine the Entity&rsquo;s Form;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&para; Determine the Entity&rsquo;s Powers;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&para; Resolve the Domination Roll;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Step One</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The caster must decide how powerful a creature&mdash; expressed in terms of Hit Dice&mdash;he will attempt to summon. This cannot be more than two times the caster's level, but this effective level for this purpose can be modified by Thaumaturgic Circles and Sacrifices&mdash;see below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Step Two</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The caster must make a saving throw versus Magic. Failing this saving throw means a more powerful creature than anticipated might come through the tear in the fabric of reality, which can have dire consequences for all present.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Step Three</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The creature's form and powers will be randomly determined on the following tables, with different results altering the creature's basic stats. Those default stats are: AC12, 1 attack for 1d6 damage, Move 120' (ground), ML10. To determine the creature&rsquo;s basic form, roll 1d12 if the original casting save was made, 1d20 if it was not.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tables in core rulebook page 134 ~ 136.</p>","memorized":0,"cast":0,"save":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"StAYtEi0AtlPHrBE":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.htkZboik4gzOTN0I"}},"_id":"XmffFqZtPq7rmEXm"}
