{"_id":"zujOWBMZj3oIGDvr","name":"Mirror Image (Magic-User Level 2)","type":"spell","img":"/systems/lotfp/assets/default/spell.png","data":{"lvl":2,"class":"Magic-User","duration":"1 Round/level","range":"0","roll":"","description":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This spell grabs 1d4 duplicates of the caster from near-identical timelines to confuse foes and make it more difficult for the original caster to come to harm. Since all of the mirror images are the caster, in the same situation and fighting the same battle in their own timeline, they are indistinguishable in every way from the caster and mimic his every motion. When an opponent makes a successful attack against one of the duplicates, it instantly dies and dissipates into nothingness (the others remain). If an opponent attempts to attack a Magic-User obscured by this spell, it is randomly determined whether the to-hit roll is directed toward the caster or one of the duplicates. Note that the duplicates do not take independent action; they are just &ldquo;mirror images&rdquo; as the spell name implies.</p>","memorized":0,"cast":0,"save":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"StAYtEi0AtlPHrBE":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.blnMwhigvIhY9f6E"}}}
{"name":"Read Magic (Magic-User Level 1)","type":"spell","img":"/systems/lotfp/assets/default/spell.png","data":{"lvl":1,"class":"Magic-User","duration":"Instantaneous","range":"0","roll":"","description":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">By means of Read Magic, the caster can decipher magical inscriptions on objects&mdash;books, scrolls, weapons, and the like&mdash;that would otherwise be unintelligible. This does not normally invoke the magic contained in the writing, although it can do so in the case of a cursed scroll. Furthermore, once the spell is cast and the caster has read the magical inscription, he thereafter is able to read that particular writing without recourse to the use of Read Magic. All spellbooks are written such that only the Elf or Magic-User who owns the book can decipher it without the use of this spell. Each casting of the spell allows the reading of 1d4 items. If a character loses access to Read Magic (a spellbook is stolen or destroyed, for instance), the character must research the spell as if it was unknown to him and then written up in a new spellbook.</p>","memorized":0,"cast":0,"save":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DeUvbLouwh3CSjte":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cfCLFILCMGHM37VG"}},"_id":"MKfcRlUrEEAMj0A8"}
